        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 3:49PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 349 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 5 miles
west of Tontitown, moving northeast at 65 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Northwest Arkansas Regional Air...Beaver Lake...
Cincinnati...                     Savoy...
Tontitown...                      Larue...
Pea Ridge...                      Cave Springs...
Wedington...                      Pleasant Ridge...
Gallitin...                       Hobbs State Park...
Lincoln...                        Busch...
War Eagle...                      Strickler...
Highfill...                       Vaughn...
Monte Ne...                       Drake Field Airport...

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 50 and 93.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
